4. SPL Basics

Structure

index=windowslogs <conditions> | <commands>

	•	Left side → Filtering
	•	Right side (|) → Processing

⸻

5. Free Text Search

index=windowslogs alice

Explanation
	•	Searches any field
	•	Case-insensitive
	•	Good for:
	•	Unknown fields
	•	Quick hunting

⸻

6. Search Operators

⸻

A. Relational Operators

Operator	Example	Explanation
=	User=James	Exact match
!=	User!=SYSTEM	Exclude value
<	Age<10	Less than
>	Traffic>50	Greater than


⸻

Example

index=windowslogs AccountName!=SYSTEM

→ Removes system noise

⸻

B. Logical Operators

Operator	Example	Explanation
AND	User=James AND EventID=4624	Both conditions
OR	User=James OR User=Alice	Either
NOT	NOT User=*	Field missing
IN	User IN (James,Alice)	Multiple match


⸻

Example

index=windowslogs AccountName!=SYSTEM AccountName=James

Explanation
	•	AND is implied
	•	Returns only James (not SYSTEM)

⸻

C. Wildcards

Image=*.exe
SourceIp=192.168.*

Explanation
	•	* = anything
	•	Useful for:
	•	Partial matches
	•	Unknown values

⸻

D. CIDR Search

SourceIp=192.168.1.0/24

Explanation
	•	Matches IP subnet
	•	Useful for network analysis

⸻

7. Quotes & Order of Evaluation

⸻

Quotes

"failed login"

	•	Exact phrase match

⸻

Order of Evaluation

Problem

alice AND bob OR charlie

Splunk interprets:

alice AND (bob OR charlie)


⸻

Correct

(alice AND bob) OR charlie


⸻

8. Pipeline Concept (|)
	•	Each command passes output to next

index=windowslogs | table User EventID


⸻

9. Filtering Commands

⸻

fields

index=windowslogs | fields User SourceIp Image

Explanation
	•	Limits visible fields
	•	Reduces noise

⸻

dedup

| dedup SourceIp

Explanation
	•	Removes duplicate values
	•	Keeps first occurrence

⸻

rename

| rename User as Employee

Explanation
	•	Improves readability

⸻

regex

| regex Image="\.exe$"

Explanation
	•	Matches pattern
	•	$ = end of string

⸻

10. Structuring Commands

⸻

table

index=windowslogs | table _time User EventID SourceIp

Explanation
	•	Creates clean output
	•	Best for:
	•	Reports
	•	Timelines

⸻

head / tail

| head 10
| tail 10

	•	First / last events

⸻

sort

| sort User


⸻

reverse

| reverse


⸻

11. Timeline Example

index=windowslogs Hostname=PC1
| table _time EventID User
| reverse

→ Shows chronological activity

